I have completely built out a new, advanced useState project inside 10-usestate-advance.

What makes it "Advanced"?
Instead of managing a simple primitive, like a single number or a string (which we did in your counter project), this project manages an entire object in a single useState hook.

Here's how it works:

Object State: The state profile holds an object with name, role, and bio.
The Spread Operator (...): We use a single, reusable handleChange function for all the inputs. When updating an object in React, you can't just update one field—you have to create a new object and merge the old fields while applying the new ones. You'll see ...prevProfile happening in App.jsx, which is an essential pattern to learn!
Live Sync: You have a beautiful live preview card on the left side (or top on mobile) that instantly updates as you type in the editor form on the right.
The Design
Just like your previous app, I focused on visual excellence:

Used a beautiful deep teal gradient background.
Clean glassmorphism (frosted glass) effects on the container.
An automatically generated circular avatar that derives initials from the name input.
Animated inputs that glow cyan when you focus on them.
